    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I did not fail to inform my Government of
                            the arrangements made whereby the United States Fish Commission steamer
                                <hi rend="italic">Albatross</hi> has been placed at the disposal of
                            the scientists appointed by both Governments, respectively, to carry on
                            inquiries during the present season into the condition of the fur-seal
                            fisheries in Bering Sea and at the Commander Islands.</p>
                <p>I am now in receipt of a dispatch from the Marquis of Salisbury, in which
                            I am directed by his lordship to convey to you the thanks of Her
                            Majesty’s Government for the facilities thus extended to Mr. D’Arcy
                            Thompson and Mr. Macoun in the prosecution of their investigations, and
                            at the same time to express the readiness of Her Majesty’s Government to
                            defray half the cost of the cruise of the <hi rend="italic">Albatross</hi>.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
